Your responsibilities:

The Senior Quality Assurance Analyst (Complaints Manager) is responsible for supporting the Senior QA Manager in delivering the development, implementation and ongoing maintenance of a QA framework and programmes of internal audits.

The Senior QA Analyst will also be responsible for the assessment of root cause analysis on ongoing complaints and E&Os, providing trend analysis and working with the business to build effective solutions. The Senior QA Analyst will take ownership of national initiatives and continuous improvement activities and will deputise for the QA Manager in their absence.

Key Duties:
Support the achievement of the company Mission & Goals relating to pensions administration;
Assist with the build of a competency framework, then continuously review, maintain and monitor it, completing risk assessments as appropriate;
Provide MI in relation to competency assessment and audits;
Carry out deep dive reviews when new processes or changes are implemented;
Act as a subject matter expert regarding business controls and the QA framework;
Undertake routine reviews of complaints and E&O’s, carrying out root cause analysis and providing feedback, learnings and process change as required;
Own given national initiatives and continuous improvement activities to support ongoing improvement and learnings;
Maintain an up to date knowledge of industry practices.
Qualifications:
Proven experience in complaints management, ideally within a pension’s administration environment;
Track in complaints management and resolution, delivering fixes and Root Cause Analysis at process, site and strategic level;
Strong understanding of occupational pensions schemes, including - DB, DC, CARE and Hybrid schemes;
Ideally QPA or PMI qualified or willing to study towards relevant qualifications;
Ability to break down and explain complex information and present them in simple terms;
The ability to evaluate, quality checks, and advise on complaints procedures;
Ability to prioritise workloads with conflicting importance, keeping to deadlines, agreed service levels and disclosure requirements;
Good understanding of various codes of professional ethics and standards as promulgated by the PMI.
